This is a trade secret 🤫 

It can be scary showing up on camera, and maybe you have a million excuses why you’re not going to film yourself today- even when you know it’s important for your brand…so let me help. 

Do you avoid filming because you don’t feel confident on camera?

As a professional model for 15 years, I’m sharing the simple shooting hack I have used on every video I’ve ever made to make me feel more comfortable on camera.

When you feel good about yourself, what you look like is one thing you don’t have to worry about, and you can focus on providing value for your audience!

Tag a fellow creator who didn’t know this!

#creatortips #iggrowth

caption.text:
Spilling the Tea☕️⬇️

If your instagram account isn’t growing
If you’re not making sales

Listen up, and make sure you have ALL 3 of these ingredients. 

You know you need to focus on one specific subject in your instagram account, but what you might not know is the different ways you need to approach this subject. 

You need to let that subject “brew” in the minds of your audience and we do this 3 different ways.

☕️Growth Content- this can include things like tips, hacks and quick actionable, funny, relatable, saveable and shareable content. To reach a wider audience and encourage them to follow.

☕️Nurture Content- this is where you can go deeper into your subject with people who chose to follow you, share your expertise, skills, opinions and experience in the industry. show your audience you know your stuff!

☕️Sales- this is where you actually talk about and promote your product and offers, and encourage your audience to take action. 

If you don’t cover all 3 of these areas regularly! Then you’re not making the “perfect cup of tea! ☕️ 

I cover this in great detail in my video masterclass, you can grab your own copy by commenting CLASS below

If you found this tip, useful, make sure you’re following me, I post new tips every day to help you on your Instagram growth journey.

Easy Hack to Share a Reel ⬇️

Instagram has confirmed that reels are the still the best way for you to reach new followers , but stories are the best way to connect to audiences….well this hack combines both, AND looks great too so you can use it again and again! 

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

- Tap and beginner new reel, add any photo you’d like to share, and press next. Go into your sparkles tab, and look for the filter “3 frames”, choose this filter, but zoom out slightly to move the effect down the screen and take a screenshot.

- Trim up the screenshot to turn your reel into an image.

- Go to the reel, you would like to share, tap the aeroplane and share to story.

- Resize the reel in the left of the screen of the screen, now go to your stickers, tab, photo album, and add the image you just created. Now the reel appears in front, and the photo behind.

- Go to your stickers tab, type “new reel white” and choose the sticker to place on top of the reel

- Now go to your stickers, tab, type click, choose your favourite, click, and place it over the top of the reel.

Anybody that taps your reel is going to get taken through to watch it. 

If you love this instagram reel idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

But remember if you want some more detailed help on how to grow your Instagram audience, comment CLASS below and I’ll send over a link that will teach you how to create outreach, growth content just like I have!

caption.text:
Reels are NOT scary!

I know video content sometimes feels scary, maybe you’re put off making reels because you don’t like the idea of videoing yourself, or you just don’t know what to say.

I’m going to start a new series of reels you can make in under one minute, so SAVE this post

- take this audio I’ve used

- add a 5 second video of your product in action, being made, you doing the thing you do or relevant clip

- add a caption calling out to your audience to “please stop” doing something and asking them to do the thing that you…

Examples below ⬇️ 

I’m tired of making content, please just book an appointment

I’m tired of repeating myself, please stop counting calories and expecting to lose weight 

Please stop second guessing yourself, and buy the necklace

Please please please, join our email list 

There are so many variations, you can use as a service based or product based business, you can add humour in your video or have it to just showcase what you do.

Let me know if you try this simple idea!

If you want to know about the full course in writing with everything you’ll ever need to know about instagram, just comment the word register below and I’ll put you on the waitlist!

Not only is this way a great way to build connection and relatability with your audience, you can call your exact audience and product or service with the on screen text!

#contentstrategy #reelsideas #instagramgrowth

Get this Viral Story Effect ⬇️

This got over 2 million views last time I used it, such a simple effect!

First off, don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps

Instructions are below ⬇️

- tap to begin a new story, go to create, slide through the filters until you find the magnifying glass.

- Tap the magnifying glass and type, “falling down cards” and use this effect

- now begin a new story, and add any image you want to use, ho to your sparkles tab, and add the filter you just saved 

- now go to your sticker tab, your photo album and add the original image into the centre of the screen.

- Now go to your sticker tab again, type instagram frame and choose the same one as me, it fits nicely over the photo in the centre of the screen.

- Now go to sticker tab one more time, type instagram like, and add this to the frame.

- Lastly, go to your sticker tab, and link, add the link to your business or brand, and place this on the white frame. 

- Finally, go to your sticker tab and search for click. Add your favourite click and anyone that taps it will be taken right through to your site or blog. 

This is such a simple effect you could use over and over again with different images and links as you need! Let me know if this tutorial helped.

I share brand new ideas daily to help inspire your instagram content and help you grow your audience and learn your way around instagram!

reusable_text_info.text: An Instagram secret, I bet you didn’t know…

caption.text:
Do the scary thing! 

🤔Maybe you’re scared to show up online? 
🙄Maybe the fear of judgement stops you posting? 
😫Maybe you don’t want to annoy your followers or friends by talking about your business again.

Let me tell you a story:
I was painfully shy and bullied terribly as a teenager, I ending up having to move to a new school but I swore after that fresh start, I would always try to be braver and do the scary thing. I went on to become a professional model with 1 million followers on instagram, who said YES to every job I was offered whether I knew how I’d manage it or not.

Because, If you wait until you feel fully ready, it might never come.

When I started a Embrace Socials, my new business in secret 

Absolutely terrified!

Writing my own digital products based on my experience on social media

Absolutely terrified 

Heck, even jumping out of an airplane at 10,000 feet, climbing a mountain or driving a tank in the name of charity

Absolutely terrified 

But I’ve done it and look where it’s got me! I’ve built this incredible community which is growing daily, today I’ve been invited to some public speaking gigs, does it frighten me…absolutely but will I do it?

You bet

Do the thing, do it scared and enjoy every moment.

If you feel comfortable tell us the thing you’re avoiding? Maybe it won’t feel so scary when others hear, and maybe they’ll be tips in the comments on how to overcome? 

#instagramgrowthexpert #iggrowth

If this hits home with you, Would you do me a HUGE favour and share this post up to your story… To tell other small business owners you know, that you support them and to remind everyone that if you love something let them know!

caption.text:
Make yourself into a gif!

If you’re shy to be filming yourself regularly but know the importance of building connection through your stories, creating yourself as a gif sticker is a great way to inject some personality into your posts!

Make sure you’re saving this post so you don’t forget the steps.

- Film yourself against a plain wall making any motion or movement with your hands. Once you’re happy, save this video.

- And begin new story, at any photo that you would like to share. Go to your stickers tab, tap the cutout button and click the video that you just made.

- Tap the sticker button, and the video created will turn into a GIF sticker, sticker anywhere on screen.

- Now go to your text tab, at any text to suit the theme of your post.

The great thing about this is once you have created the sticker you can reuse it again and again on different posts.

People buy from people they know like and trust and Stories is hands down the best place to start doing that!

Let me know if this was helpful! And maybe share with a fellow creator.

If you’re looking for a clearer idea of what stories are all about, comment CLASS and I’ll send you my 75 minute lesson that walks you through them in detail!!

caption.text:
1 photo reel ⬇️

This is one of the most SIMPLE instagram reels you will ever create, you only need one photo and instagram will do the rest! ⬇️
I’m all about working smarter, not harder.

You can theme this anyway you’d like by choosing your own text and image!! Just don’t forget to SAVE so you don’t forget!

Here is the step by step guide below:

- go to start a new reel

- Upload any image of your choice 

- Now go to the sparkles filters button and tap the magnifying glass

- Type “Polaroid by f” and select the same filter as me

- This is now a reel, move you video to right leaving border on left.

- go to stickers tab and type in moving line, use the same sticker as me and place it over the line where the reel meets the border space.

- Now just choose your favourite font, and place the text in the space on the left-hand side.

Don’t forget a useful caption Add a catchy hook, if you are struggling to come up with one, comment HOOK below and I’ll send my free guide, plus 100 captions for you try 🎁

caption.text:
Watch till the end 😂

If this is you too, Send to a small business owner who will agree 👍 

It’s tough out there, and being successful on Instagram is no simple task, not only do you need to wear a LOT of different hats, you have to do it in an ever changing Instagram Landscape!

That’s where I come in, I’m here to help you navigate Instagram with ease! If this post resonated with you, perhaps send it to a fellow business owner who might need my help! After all, we’re all in this together 🫶🏻
